It could be a bit shorter if designated initializers are used, instead of:

```cpp
Opts opts;
opts.x = 1;
opts.y = 2;
opts.z = 3;
new CNode(
    ...
    opts
);
```

it would become:

```cpp
new CNode(
    ...
    {
        .x = 1,
        .y = 2,
        .z = 3
    }
);
```

